food.name: Rendang
food.description: Rendang is a rich and tender coconut beef stew which is explosively flavorful and famous throughout Indonesia. Simmered in coconut milk and spices until the liquid evaporates, this dish is intensely flavorful with complex layers of taste from the various spices used in its preparation.

disease_rate.note: The high content of saturated fat and cholesterol can increase the risk of heart disease if consumed excessively.
The relatively high sodium content can contribute to high blood pressure if not controlled.

food.name: Hamburger
food.description: Hamburger is a sandwich consisting of a cooked patty of ground meat placed inside a sliced bread roll or bun.

disease_rate.note: High in saturated fat and sodium, which may contribute to cardiovascular issues if consumed regularly.
High caloric density may contribute to weight gain if consumed frequently.

food.name: Pizza
food.description: Pizza is a savory dish consisting of a round, flattened base of leavened wheat-based dough topped with tomatoes, cheese, and various other ingredients.

disease_rate.note: High sodium content, particularly from cheese and tomato sauce, may impact blood pressure.
Contains cheese which is high in lactose. Consider dairy-free alternatives if intolerant.

food.name: Pisang Goreng
food.description: Pisang Goreng is a popular Indonesian snack made of banana coated in batter and deep fried until golden and crispy.

disease_rate.note: High in carbohydrates and sugar, may cause spikes in blood sugar levels.
Deep-fried food, high in oil content that may affect cardiovascular health if consumed excessively.

food.name: Sop Konro
food.description: Sop Konro is a Makassar-style beef rib soup cooked with various spices like cinnamon, kluwek, tamarind, and coriander. The soup has a dark color and rich flavor.

disease_rate.note: The sodium content is quite high, excessive consumption can trigger high blood pressure.
Beef ribs contain saturated fat, limit consumption for those with high cholesterol.

food.name: Ayam Geprek
food.description: Ayam geprek is a crispy fried chicken dish that is crushed and mixed with spicy chili sauce, popular as fast food in Indonesia.

disease_rate.note: The high content of saturated fat and cholesterol can increase the risk of heart disease if consumed excessively.
The high sodium content can contribute to high blood pressure if not controlled.

food.name: Roti Bakar
food.description: Roti bakar is toasted bread usually served with various toppings such as butter, jam, cheese, or chocolate.

disease_rate.note: High carbohydrate and sugar content may elevate blood sugar levels.

food.name: Kopi Susu
food.description: Kopi susu is a beverage consisting of a mixture of coffee and milk, often with added sugar for sweetness.

disease_rate.note: High sugar content from condensed milk can affect blood sugar levels.
Caffeine can disturb sleep patterns if consumed close to bedtime.

food.name: Papeda
food.description: Papeda is a staple food from Papua and Maluku in the form of sago porridge with a chewy, sticky texture and a clear white color.

disease_rate.note: Papeda has a low glycemic index, making it relatively safe for diabetes patients when consumed in moderate portions.
Papeda is low in fat and contains no cholesterol.

food.name: Pempek
food.description: Pempek is a Palembang specialty made from fish and sago flour, served with a sour and spicy cuko sauce.

ingredients.name: Cuko sauce (palm sugar, tamarind, chili, garlic)

disease_rate.note: The sodium content is quite high, which could affect blood pressure if consumed excessively.
The carbohydrate content and cuko sauce's sugar content should be considered for diabetics.

food.name: Gudeg
food.description: Gudeg is a traditional dish from Yogyakarta made with young jackfruit cooked in coconut milk and palm sugar, resulting in a sweet and savory flavor.

disease_rate.note: Contains high sugar from palm sugar, which may affect blood glucose levels.
The sodium and fat content from coconut milk could be a concern for those with high blood pressure.

food.name: Rawon
food.description: Rawon is a black beef soup from East Java, using kluwek as a coloring agent and flavor enhancer.

disease_rate.note: The sodium content may contribute to high blood pressure if consumed excessively.
Contains beef which has saturated fats that can affect cholesterol levels.

food.name: Ayam Betutu
food.description: Ayam Betutu is a whole chicken seasoned with Balinese spices, wrapped in banana leaves, then grilled or steamed until tender.

disease_rate.note: Contains cholesterol from chicken, but less than red meat. Remove skin to reduce fat content.
The sodium from salt and spices may affect blood pressure if consumed in excess.

food.name: Lawar
food.description: Lawar is a mixture of chopped meat, vegetables, grated coconut, and Balinese spices, often served as a side dish.

disease_rate.note: Contains animal fats and coconut which are high in saturated fat. Choose chicken over pork for lower fat content.
The combination of meat, coconut, and vegetables may be heavy for sensitive digestive systems.

food.name: Gado-Gado
food.description: Gado-Gado is an Indonesian boiled vegetable salad served with peanut sauce, eggs, and crackers.

disease_rate.note: Contains peanuts as a main ingredient in the sauce. Avoid completely if allergic.
High in plant-based proteins and vegetables, with good fats from peanuts. Excellent for heart health.

food.name: Nasi Tutug Oncom
food.description: Nasi Tutug Oncom is rice mixed with fried fermented soybean cake and spices, resulting in a savory taste and distinctive aroma.

disease_rate.note: Contains high carbohydrate content from rice. Portion control is recommended for diabetics.
Fermented oncom contains probiotics that may support healthy gut flora.

food.name: Karedok
food.description: Karedok is a traditional Sundanese salad made from raw vegetables like long beans, bean sprouts, eggplant, and cabbage, dressed with peanut sauce.

disease_rate.note: Contains peanuts in the sauce. Avoid if allergic.
High in raw vegetables with fiber, supporting digestive health and nutrient absorption.

food.name: Pecel
food.description: Pecel is a mixture of boiled vegetables such as spinach, long beans, and bean sprouts, served with spicy peanut sauce.

disease_rate.note: Contains peanuts in the sauce. Avoid if allergic.
Good source of iron from spinach and other vegetables, helpful for preventing anemia.

food.name: Sayur Asem
food.description: Sayur asem is a fresh sour soup containing long beans, corn, chayote, and melinjo, popular as a home-cooked meal.

disease_rate.note: Low in calories and high in fiber, making it a good option for those managing weight.
Low glycemic index and minimal sugar content make it suitable for diabetics.

food.name: Soto Ayam
food.description: Soto Ayam is a chicken soup with yellow turmeric broth, served with rice vermicelli, eggs, and celery.

disease_rate.note: Warm broth and anti-inflammatory properties of turmeric may help soothe respiratory issues.
Watch salt content for those with high blood pressure.

food.name: Tinutuan
food.description: Tinutuan is a Manado porridge consisting of various vegetables such as water spinach, spinach, corn, sweet potatoes, and basil leaves.

disease_rate.note: Contains carbohydrates from rice and sweet potatoes, but the fiber from vegetables helps moderate blood sugar spikes.
Very low in fat and cholesterol, while providing essential vitamins and minerals for cardiovascular health.

food.name: Pepes Ikan Kembung
food.description: Pepes ikan kembung is mackerel seasoned with spices, wrapped in banana leaves and then steamed.

disease_rate.note: Rich in omega-3 fatty acids from mackerel that support cardiovascular health.
Good source of calcium and vitamin D for strong bones.

food.name: Mie Aceh
food.description: Mie Aceh is thick yellow noodles with curry-like spices, containing beef/shrimp/crab and vegetables.

disease_rate.note: Higher sodium content from noodles and seasoning may affect blood pressure.
Contains refined carbohydrates in noodles which may affect blood sugar levels.

food.name: Sate Ayam
food.description: Sate ayam is skewered grilled chicken served with peanut sauce and rice cake.

disease_rate.note: Contains peanut sauce which is a major allergen. Avoid completely if allergic.
Sweet soy sauce contains high sugar, which may affect blood glucose levels.
